.TH addwstr 3
.SH NAME
\*Laddwstr\*O, \*Laddnwstr\*O, \*Lwaddwstr\*O, \*Lwaddnwstr\*O, \*Lmvaddwstr\*O, \*Lmvaddnwstr\*O, \*Lmvwaddwstr\*O, \*Lmvwaddnwstr\*O \- Add a string of wchar_t characters to a curses window and advance cursor
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
The \*Lcurses\*O library (\*Llibcurses.so\*O, \*Llibcurses.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O
.PP
\*Lint addwstr( wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);
.PP
\*Lint addnwstr(
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn\*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint waddwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint waddnwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvaddwstr(
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvaddnwstr(
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvwaddwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr \*L);\*O
.PP
\*Lint mvwaddnwstr(
.br
        WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L,
.br
        int \*Vy\*L,
.br
        int \*Vx\*L,
.br
        wchar_t \(**\*Vwstr\*L,
.br
        int \*Vn \*L);\*O
.sE
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
.VL
.LI "\*Vwstr\*O"
Specifies the wide-character string to be added to the window.
.LI "\*Vwin\*O"
Specifies a \*Lcurses\*O window. If not specified, the
window is the default window \*Lstdscr\*O.
.LI "\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O"
Specifies the line (\*Vy\*O) and column (\*Vx\*O)
coordinates of the target position on the window.
If coordinates are not specified, the target
position is the current position of the logical cursor.
.LI "\*Vn\*O"
Specifies the maximum number of wide characters to be added
from the string.
.LE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "addwstr macro"
.iX "addnwstr macro"
.iX "waddwstr macro"
.iX "waddnwstr function"
.iX "mvaddwstr macro"
.iX "mvaddnwstr macro"
.iX "mvwaddwstr macro"
.iX "mvwaddnwstr macro"
The \*Laddwstr\*O routine writes all the characters of the
null-terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the default window at the current (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Laddnwstr\*O routine writes at most \*Vn\*O characters of the
null-terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the default window at the current (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lwaddwstr\*O routine writes all the characters of the
null terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the specified window at the current (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lwaddnwstr\*O routine writes at most \*Vn\*O characters of the
null terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the specified window at the current (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lmvaddwstr\*O routine
writes all the characters of the
null terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the default window at the specified (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lmvaddnwstr\*O routine
writes at most \*Vn\*O characters of the
null terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the default window at the specified (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lmvwaddwstr\*O routine writes all the characters of the
null terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the specified window at the specified (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The \*Lmvwaddnwstr\*O routine writes at most \*Vn\*O characters of the
null terminated wchar_t character string \*Vwstr\*O
on the specified window at the specified (\*Vy\*O, \*Vx\*O) coordinates.
.PP
The following information applies to all the routines:
.ML
.LI
\*LERR\*O is returned
if writing the string causes illegal scrolling.
.IP
In this case,
the routine writes as much as possible of the string
on the window.
.LI
The routines are functionally
equivalent to calling \*Laddwch\*O or \*Lwaddwch\*O
once for each wchar_t character in the string.
.LE
.PP
The
\*Laddwstr\*O, \*Laddnwstr\*O, \*Lwaddwstr\*O,
\*Lmvaddwstr\*O, \*Lmvaddnwstr\*O, \*Lmvwaddwstr\*O and \*Lmvwaddnwstr\*O
routines are macros.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Laddwstr\*O, \*Laddnwstr\*O, \*Lwaddwstr\*O, \*Lwaddnwstr\*O,
\*Lmvaddwstr\*O, \*Lmvaddnwstr\*O, \*Lmvwaddwstr\*O, and \*Lmvwaddnwstr\*O
routines return \*LOK\*O on success and \*LERR\*O on error.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
Functions: \*Laddwch\*O(3), \*Laddwchstr\*O(3), \*Lcurses\*O(3),
\*Lcurses_intro\*O(3), \*Linswstr\*O(3).
